Care instructions Machine Wash, Hand Wash Only

🌸Experience ultimate comfort with our women's cotton underwear: No pilling, pinching, shrinking, or fading. Our soft, high-quality cotton has fine stretch and permeability, and the wide elastic waistband ensures no rolling down or cutting into your legs. Say goodbye to wedgies and bunching, and hello to all-day comfort.

🌸Enjoy full coverage and nice stretch with our panties: The double-layered front panel helps retain heat to ease cramps and offers more protection for your health. Our panties are super soft and comfortable to wear all day, and they won't stretch out through the day. Plus, they give you more room to move and breathe while hugging your hips and even curving up and around your butt to hug your waist.

🌸Our stylish and high-waisted underwear briefs are perfect for all female friends, junior teen girls, maternity, mothers, and grandmas. The high waist offers enough support for postpartum c-section and abdominal surgery recovery, and it's kind of like shapewear for women's tummy control.

🌸Washing our cotton underpants is a breeze: You can hand wash them or machine wash them with a laundry bag (30°C Max), and they'll dry great without any uncomfortable elastic against your skin. These high-rise cotton underwear are perfect for daily wear at home, as well as for workout, running, yoga, dinner, work, bedtime, and everyday use.

🌸At VIVISOO, we focus on high-quality intimates inspired by vision and softness. Our fluorescent colors are cute, sexy, and sporty, while our dark color combinations exude mature charm and luxury. Our black panties pack is a classic and forever love. Plus, our material is soft and breathable, keeping you comfortable all day long.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Slightly different design then the others I ordered.
reviews.reviewText: These are comfortable and they leave no panty lines. They also hold in any little extra you may want to hide. I ordered a large due to I have wide hips (42.5 inches) and a petite ish frame. They work great and half my butt doesn't fall out.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars My favorite undies
reviews.reviewText: I found these over a year ago and they are the only undies I will buy from now on. They fit amazing and are nice and soft. I’m a big girl so it’s difficult for me to find undies in my size that are a comfortable cut and fit well. These check every box!!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Super comfortable and surprisingly good quality
reviews.reviewText: I chose these originally because they were cheap, they weren't too overly feminine or masculine, and they came in my size. I'm a larger person so it's hard to find decent quality clothing big enough to fit me. To my surprise, these have got to be some of the most comfortable underwear I've ever had. I'm straight up replacing all my old ones with these now. They are also great quality, which I didn't necessarily expect for the price point and for a generic seeming brand on Amazon I've never even heard of before. The fabric is super soft and stretchy, the seams are super well done, the color doesn't bleed, the band does its job without digging in, it takes a LOT for them to get swampy and gross, and they seem sturdy enough to last a long time. Definitely better than the underwear packs I used to get at Walmart. They fit true to the size chart. I guess if you like your underwear tight you could go a size down, I personally wouldn't though. If you're on the fence, go for it!

reviews.reviewText: I do like these, as the softness & comfort are wonderful. But I really prefer the hipsters in this brand that I bought previously, as the fit is better. Hope Amazon brings them back!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on December 18, 2022
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Went up 2 sizes & They Are Wonderful
reviews.reviewText: It's been a minute since I've been able to give something 5 stars on Amazon, but hooray we have a winner!! 🎉🎉✔I loved the cute mock "tightie whitie" style of these undies, like a combo between boy shorts & panties or something.I toiled overtime deciding what size to get. Currently a plus-sized beauty, I scoured the reviews, & between those & the sizing guide I did go up 2 full sizes larger than what I usually wear. I'm So Glad I ordered up. I went up the 2 sizes mostly because other reviewers mentioned the leg holes being too tight. And yes, they ARE too tight so you will wanna size up for sure IMO. Even w the 2 size jump-up I almost returned these because of the leg hole issue. Fortunately they do give a little after wearing them a bit, so crisis averted.Fyi poor blood circulation in your hips can literally cause osteoarthritis (#speakingfromexperience) so over the years all our tight panties, jeans, leggings etc can actually do a number on our blood supply in those areas so I'm extra careful about underwear pulling tight in the leg hole area & jeopardizing circulation. If I'm not mistaken it's actually where your femoral artery is located, which brings all the blood to your legs.Biology lesson aside, these underwear are well-made, well-designed, super soft & comfy, and even wash well so far. They're quite thick, actually, which make them more substantial, in a good way.They literally make me FEEL better because they cover well, are so comfortable, and not so bad to look at in the mirror, either. Pleasantly covers any unsightly lower belly (fupah) and hugs your bum in the exact right location to create proper cheek definition. 😄I'm hoping the price won't skyrocket before I can afford to grab another bunch of them.Like every woman knows, when something fits, get multiples!
